CHAT.comment: Book Reading; The Very Hungry Caterpillar

Chi reads pretty well; Mot corrects individual words that are read (or pronounced) incorrectly , or questions the word , which Chi then reads correctly without much trouble; Mot suggests that Chi take her time and look at the fruit; CHi has more trouble at second half of book than at beginning , either through fatigue or because it's more complicated and less obvious what the text is; context notes say Mot points to words now and then to help Chi with pronunciation
